Re: Bitcoin 0.3.2 released

Bitcointalk

2010-07-18 18:58:21 UTC - [11]Original Post

   The change list is basically encompassed by whatʼs listed in the first
   message.  Everyone should upgrade to get the important security
   improvements.
   Minimizing to tray had at least 3 different glitches and bugs on Linux,
   including a crash one, so I disabled it again.  You can still re-enable
   the option with "-minimizetotray" if you want to use it anyway.  The
   bugs/glitches are somewhere in wxWidgets or GTK or Gnome and I donʼt
   know how to fix them.  Sorry, I just donʼt know what else to do, itʼs
   just too glitchy and buggy to have as a mainline feature.
